#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an8.12"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an8.12:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 8 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 8 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.12:0.2"
msgid "2. Mahāvagga "
msgstr "2. The Great Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 12. Sīhasutta → sīhasotāpatisuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an8.12:0.3"
msgid "12. Sīhasutta "
msgstr "12. With Sīha "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an8.12:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof. "

msgctxt "an8.12:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā abhiññātā abhiññātā licchavī santhāgāre sannisinnā sannipatitā anekapariyāyena buddhassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti, dhammassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti, saṃghassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti. "
msgstr "Now at that time several very prominent Licchavis were sitting together at the meeting hall, praising the Buddha, his teaching, and the Saṅgha in many ways. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.180, sc2
msgctxt "an8.12:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sīho senāpati nigaṇṭhasāvako tassaṃ parisāyaṃ nisinno hoti. "
msgstr "Now at that time General Sīha, a disciple of the Jains, was sitting in that assembly. "

msgctxt "an8.12:2.2"
msgid "Atha kho sīhassa senāpatissa etadahosi: "
msgstr "He thought, "

msgctxt "an8.12:2.3"
msgid "“nissaṃsayaṃ kho so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho bhavissati, tathā hime sambahulā abhiññātā abhiññātā licchavī santhāgāre sannisinnā sannipatitā anekapariyāyena buddhassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti, dhammassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti, saṃghassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti. "
msgstr "“That Blessed One must certainly be a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha. For several very prominent Licchavis are praising the Buddha, his teaching, and the Saṅgha in many ways. "

msgctxt "an8.12:2.4"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ taṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkameyyaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhan”ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t I go to see that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: nāṭaputto → nātaputto (bj) | nāthaputto (si)
msgctxt "an8.12:2.5"
msgid "Atha kho sīho senāpati yena nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then General Sīha went to Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta and said to him, "

msgctxt "an8.12:2.6"
msgid "“icchāmahaṃ, bhante, samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamitun”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, I’d like to go to see the ascetic Gotama.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an8.12:3.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, sīha, kiriyavādo samāno akiriyavādaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissasi? "
msgstr "“But Sīha, you believe in the doctrine of action. Why should you go to see the ascetic Gotama, who teaches a doctrine of inaction? "

msgctxt "an8.12:3.2"
msgid "Samaṇo hi, sīha, gotamo akiriyavādo, akiriyāya dhammaṃ deseti, tena ca sāvake vinetī”ti. "
msgstr "For the ascetic Gotama believes in a doctrine of inaction, he teaches inaction, and he guides his disciples in that way.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: gamiyābhisaṅkhāro → gamikābhisaṅkhāro (si)
msgctxt "an8.12:3.3"
msgid "Atha kho sīhassa senāpatissa yo ahosi gamiyābhisaṅkhāro bhagavantaṃ dassanāya, so paṭippassambhi. "
msgstr "Then Sīha’s determination to go and see the Buddha died down. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.181, sc4
msgctxt "an8.12:4.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho sambahulā abhiññātā abhiññātā licchavī santhāgāre sannisinnā sannipatitā anekapariyāyena buddhassa … pe … dhammassa … pe … saṅghassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti. "
msgstr "For a second time, several prominent Licchavis were sitting together at the meeting hall, praising the Buddha, his teaching, and the Saṅgha in many ways. "

msgctxt "an8.12:4.2"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho sīhassa senāpatissa etadahosi: "
msgstr "And for a second time Sīha thought: "

msgctxt "an8.12:4.3"
msgid "“nissaṃsayaṃ kho so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho bhavissati, tathā hime sambahulā abhiññātā abhiññātā licchavī santhāgāre sannisinnā sannipatitā anekapariyāyena buddhassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti, dhammassa … pe … saṅghassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.12:4.4"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ taṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkameyyaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhan”ti. "
msgstr "“Why don’t I go to see that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.12:4.5"
msgid "Atha kho sīho senāpati yena nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then General Sīha went to Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta … "

msgctxt "an8.12:4.6"
msgid "“icchāmahaṃ, bhante, samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamitun”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an8.12:5.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, sīha, kiriyavādo samāno akiriyavādaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissasi? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.12:5.2"
msgid "Samaṇo hi, sīha, gotamo akiriyavādo akiriyāya dhammaṃ deseti, tena ca sāvake vinetī”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.12:5.3"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho sīhassa senāpatissa yo ahosi gamiyābhisaṅkhāro bhagavantaṃ dassanāya, so paṭippassambhi. "
msgstr "Then for a second time Sīha’s determination to go and see the Buddha died down. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an8.12:6.1"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho sambahulā abhiññātā abhiññātā licchavī santhāgāre sannisinnā sannipatitā anekapariyāyena buddhassa … pe … dhammassa … pe … saṃghassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti. "
msgstr "For a third time, several prominent Licchavis were sitting together at the meeting hall, praising the Buddha, his teaching, and the Saṅgha in many ways. "

msgctxt "an8.12:6.2"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho sīhassa senāpatissa etadahosi: "
msgstr "And for a third time Sīha thought, "

msgctxt "an8.12:6.3"
msgid "“nissaṃsayaṃ kho so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho bhavissati, tathā hime sambahulā abhiññātā abhiññātā licchavī santhāgāre sannisinnā sannipatitā anekapariyāyena buddhassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti, dhammassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti, saṃghassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti. "
msgstr "“That Blessed One must certainly be a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha. For several very prominent Licchavis are praising the Buddha, his teaching, and the Saṅgha in many ways. "

# NOTE: BB has “permission” for apalokita, but there’s no sense of that in the dialogue. mahavira never tells him he can’t go, he just tries to dissuade him. At SN 22.81 the Buddha is said to leave without apalokita with the sangha, so it can hardly mean permission.
msgctxt "an8.12:6.4"
msgid "Kiṃ hime karissanti nigaṇṭhā apalokitā vā anapalokitā vā? "
msgstr "What can these Jains do to me, whether I consult with them or not? "

#. VAR: nigaṇṭhe → nigaṇṭhaṃ (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "an8.12:6.5"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ anapaloketvāva nigaṇṭhe taṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkameyyaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhan”ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t I, without consulting them, go to see that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an8.12:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho sīho senāpati pañcamattehi rathasatehi divādivassa vesāliyā niyyāsi bhagavantaṃ dassanāya. "
msgstr "Then Sīha, with around five hundred chariots, set out from Vesālī in the middle of the day to see the Buddha. "

# NOTE: BB follows PTS, which has arame pavisi.
msgctxt "an8.12:7.2"
msgid "Yāvatikā yānassa bhūmi, yānena gantvā yānā paccorohitvā pattikova agamāsi. "
msgstr "He went by carriage as far as the terrain allowed, then descended and went by foot. "

msgctxt "an8.12:7.3"
msgid "Atha kho sīho senāpati yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho sīho senāpati bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then General Sīha went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.182, sc8
msgctxt "an8.12:8.1"
msgid "“Sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante: "
msgstr "“Sir, I have heard this: "

msgctxt "an8.12:8.2"
msgid "‘akiriyavādo samaṇo gotamo, akiriyāya dhammaṃ deseti, tena ca sāvake vinetī’ti. "
msgstr "‘The ascetic Gotama believes in a doctrine of inaction, he teaches inaction, and he guides his disciples in that way.’ "

#. VAR: vādānuvādo → vādānupāto (si, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an8.12:8.3"
msgid "Ye te, bhante, evamāhaṃsu: ‘akiriyavādo samaṇo gotamo, akiriyāya dhammaṃ deseti, tena ca sāvake vinetī’ti, kacci te, bhante, bhagavato vuttavādino na ca bhagavantaṃ abhūtena abbhācikkhanti dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākaronti na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgacchati? "
msgstr "I trust those who say this repeat what the Buddha has said, and do not misrepresent him with an untruth? Is their explanation in line with the teaching? Are there any legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism? "

msgctxt "an8.12:8.4"
msgid "Anabbhakkhātukāmā hi mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantan”ti. "
msgstr "For we don’t want to misrepresent the Blessed One.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an8.12:9.1"
msgid "“Atthi, sīha, pariyāyo, yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya: "
msgstr "“There is, Sīha, a sense in which you could rightly say that "

msgctxt "an8.12:9.2"
msgid "‘akiriyavādo samaṇo gotamo, akiriyāya dhammaṃ deseti, tena ca sāvake vinetī’ti. (1) "
msgstr "I believe in inaction, I teach inaction, and I guide my disciples in that way. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an8.12:10.1"
msgid "Atthi, sīha, pariyāyo, yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya: "
msgstr "And there is a sense in which you could rightly say that "

msgctxt "an8.12:10.2"
msgid "‘kiriyavādo samaṇo gotamo, kiriyāya dhammaṃ deseti, tena ca sāvake vinetī’ti. (2) "
msgstr "I believe in action, I teach action, and I guide my disciples in that way. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "an8.12:11.1"
msgid "Atthi, sīha, pariyāyo, yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya: "
msgstr "And there is a sense in which you could rightly say that "

msgctxt "an8.12:11.2"
msgid "‘ucchedavādo samaṇo gotamo, ucchedāya dhammaṃ deseti, tena ca sāvake vinetī’ti. (3) "
msgstr "I believe in annihilationism, I teach annihilation, and I guide my disciples in that way. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "an8.12:12.1"
msgid "Atthi, sīha, pariyāyo, yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya: "
msgstr "And there is a sense in which you could rightly say that "

msgctxt "an8.12:12.2"
msgid "‘jegucchī samaṇo gotamo, jegucchitāya dhammaṃ deseti, tena ca sāvake vinetī’ti. (4) "
msgstr "I’m disgusted, I teach disgust, and I guide my disciples in that way. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "an8.12:13.1"
msgid "Atthi, sīha, pariyāyo, yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya: "
msgstr "And there is a sense in which you could rightly say that "

msgctxt "an8.12:13.2"
msgid "‘venayiko samaṇo gotamo, vinayāya dhammaṃ deseti, tena ca sāvake vinetī’ti. (5) "
msgstr "I'm an exterminator, I teach extermination, and I guide my disciples in that way. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "an8.12:14.1"
msgid "Atthi, sīha, pariyāyo, yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya: "
msgstr "And there is a sense in which you could rightly say that "

msgctxt "an8.12:14.2"
msgid "‘tapassī samaṇo gotamo, tapassitāya dhammaṃ deseti, tena ca sāvake vinetī’ti. (6) "
msgstr "I’m a mortifier, I teach mortification, and I guide my disciples in that way. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "an8.12:15.1"
msgid "Atthi, sīha, pariyāyo, yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya: "
msgstr "And there is a sense in which you could rightly say that "

msgctxt "an8.12:15.2"
msgid "‘apagabbho samaṇo gotamo, apagabbhatāya dhammaṃ deseti, tena ca sāvake vinetī’ti. (7) "
msgstr "I’m an abortionist, I teach abortion, and I guide my disciples in that way. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "an8.12:16.1"
msgid "Atthi, sīha, pariyāyo, yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya: "
msgstr "And there is a sense in which you could rightly say that "

msgctxt "an8.12:16.2"
msgid "‘assāsako samaṇo gotamo, assāsāya dhammaṃ deseti, tena ca sāvake vinetī’ti. (8) "
msgstr "I’m ambitious, I teach ambition, and I guide my disciples in that way. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.183, sc17
msgctxt "an8.12:17.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, sīha, pariyāyo, yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya: "
msgstr "And what’s the sense in which you could rightly say that "

msgctxt "an8.12:17.2"
msgid "‘akiriyavādo samaṇo gotamo, akiriyāya dhammaṃ deseti, tena ca sāvake vinetī’ti? "
msgstr "I believe in inaction, I teach inaction, and I guide my disciples in that way? "

msgctxt "an8.12:17.3"
msgid "Ahañhi, sīha, akiriyaṃ vadāmi kāyaduccaritassa vacīduccaritassa manoduccaritassa; "
msgstr "I teach inaction regarding bad bodily, verbal, and mental conduct, "

msgctxt "an8.12:17.4"
msgid "anekavihitānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ akiriyaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr "and the many kinds of unskillful things. "

msgctxt "an8.12:17.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, sīha, pariyāyo, yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya: "
msgstr "In this sense you could rightly say that I teach inaction. "

msgctxt "an8.12:17.6"
msgid "‘akiriyavādo samaṇo gotamo, akiriyāya dhammaṃ deseti, tena ca sāvake vinetī’ti. (1) "
msgstr " "

