msgid "Ahañhi, sīha, vinayāya dhammaṃ desemi rāgassa dosassa mohassa; "
msgstr "I teach the extermination of greed, hate, and delusion, "

msgctxt "an8.12:21.4"
msgid "anekavihitānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ vinayāya dhammaṃ desemi. "
msgstr "and the many kinds of unskillful things. "

msgctxt "an8.12:21.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, sīha, pariyāyo, yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya: "
msgstr "In this sense you could rightly say that I’m an exterminator. "

msgctxt "an8.12:21.6"
msgid "‘venayiko samaṇo gotamo, vinayāya dhammaṃ deseti, tena ca sāvake vinetī’ti. (5) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc22
msgctxt "an8.12:22.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, sīha, pariyāyo, yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya: "
msgstr "And what’s the sense in which you could rightly say that "

msgctxt "an8.12:22.2"
msgid "‘tapassī samaṇo gotamo, tapassitāya dhammaṃ deseti, tena ca sāvake vinetī’ti? "
msgstr "I’m a mortifier, I teach mortification, and I guide my disciples in that way? "

msgctxt "an8.12:22.3"
msgid "Tapanīyāhaṃ, sīha, pāpake akusale dhamme vadāmi kāyaduccaritaṃ vacīduccaritaṃ manoduccaritaṃ. "
msgstr "I say that bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind should be mortified. "

msgctxt "an8.12:22.4"
msgid "Yassa kho, sīha, tapanīyā pāpakā akusalā dhammā pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā, tamahaṃ ‘tapassī’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "I say that a mortifier is someone who has given up unskillful qualities that should be mortified. They’ve cut them off at the root, made them like a palm stump, obliterated them, so that they’re unable to arise in the future. "

msgctxt "an8.12:22.5"
msgid "Tathāgatassa kho, sīha, tapanīyā pāpakā akusalā dhammā pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā. "
msgstr "The Realized One is someone who has given up unskillful qualities that should be mortified. He has cut them off at the root, made them like a palm stump, obliterated them, so that they’re unable to arise in the future. "

msgctxt "an8.12:22.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, sīha, pariyāyo, yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya: "
msgstr "In this sense you could rightly say that I’m a mortifier. "

msgctxt "an8.12:22.7"
msgid "‘tapassī samaṇo gotamo, tapassitāya dhammaṃ deseti, tena ca sāvake vinetī’ti. (6) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc23
msgctxt "an8.12:23.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, sīha, pariyāyo, yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya: "
msgstr "And what’s the sense in which you could rightly say that "

msgctxt "an8.12:23.2"
msgid "‘apagabbho samaṇo gotamo, apagabbhatāya dhammaṃ deseti, tena ca sāvake vinetī’ti? "
msgstr "I’m an abortionist, I teach abortion, and I guide my disciples in that way? "

msgctxt "an8.12:23.3"
msgid "Yassa kho, sīha, āyatiṃ gabbhaseyyā punabbhavābhinibbatti pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā, tamahaṃ ‘apagabbho’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "I say that an abortionist is someone who has given up future wombs and rebirth into a new state of existence. They’ve cut them off at the root, made them like a palm stump, obliterated them, so that they’re unable to arise in the future. "

msgctxt "an8.12:23.4"
msgid "Tathāgatassa kho, sīha, āyatiṃ gabbhaseyyā punabbhavābhinibbatti pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā. "
msgstr "The Realized One has given up future wombs and rebirth into a new state of existence. He has cut them off at the root, made them like a palm stump, obliterated them, so that they’re unable to arise in the future. "

msgctxt "an8.12:23.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, sīha, pariyāyo, yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya: "
msgstr "In this sense you could rightly say that I’m an abortionist. "

msgctxt "an8.12:23.6"
msgid "‘apagabbho samaṇo gotamo, apagabbhatāya dhammaṃ deseti, tena ca sāvake vinetī’ti. (7) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.185, sc24
msgctxt "an8.12:24.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, sīha, pariyāyo, yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya: "
msgstr "And what’s the sense in which you could rightly say that "

msgctxt "an8.12:24.2"
msgid "‘assāsako samaṇo gotamo, assāsāya dhammaṃ deseti, tena ca sāvake vinetī’ti? "
msgstr "I’m ambitious, I teach ambition, and I guide my disciples in that way? "

msgctxt "an8.12:24.3"
msgid "Ahañhi, sīha, assāsako paramena assāsena, assāsāya dhammaṃ desemi, tena ca sāvake vinemi. "
msgstr "I’m ambitious to offer solace, the highest solace, I teach solace, and I guide my disciples in that way. "

msgctxt "an8.12:24.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, sīha, pariyāyo, yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya: "
msgstr "In this sense you could rightly say that I’m ambitious.” "

msgctxt "an8.12:24.5"
msgid "‘assāsako samaṇo gotamo, assāsāya dhammaṃ deseti, tena ca sāvake vinetī’”ti. (8) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc25
msgctxt "an8.12:25.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, sīho senāpati bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, General Sīha said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "an8.12:25.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante … pe … "
msgstr "“Excellent, sir! Excellent! "

msgctxt "an8.12:25.3"
msgid "upāsakaṃ maṃ, bhante, bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti. "
msgstr "From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc26
msgctxt "an8.12:26.1"
msgid "“Anuviccakāraṃ kho, sīha, karohi. Anuviccakāro tumhādisānaṃ ñātamanussānaṃ sādhu hotī”ti. "
msgstr "“Sīha, you should act after careful consideration. It’s good for well-known people such as yourself to act after careful consideration.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.12:26.2"
msgid "“Imināpāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato bhiyyoso mattāya attamano abhiraddho, yaṃ maṃ bhagavā evamāha: ‘anuviccakāraṃ kho, sīha, karohi. Anuviccakāro tumhādisānaṃ ñātamanussānaṃ sādhu hotī’ti. "
msgstr "“Now I’m even more delighted and satisfied with the Buddha, since he tells me to act after careful consideration. "

msgctxt "an8.12:26.3"
msgid "Mañhi, bhante, aññatitthiyā sāvakaṃ labhitvā kevalakappaṃ vesāliṃ paṭākaṃ parihareyyuṃ: "
msgstr "For if the followers of other paths were to gain me as a disciple, they’d carry a banner all over Vesālī, saying: "

msgctxt "an8.12:26.4"
msgid "‘sīho amhākaṃ senāpati sāvakattaṃ upagato’ti. "
msgstr "‘General Sīha has become our disciple!’ "

msgctxt "an8.12:26.5"
msgid "Atha ca pana bhagavā evamāha: ‘anuviccakāraṃ, sīha, karohi. Anuviccakāro tumhādisānaṃ ñātamanussānaṃ sādhu hotī’ti. "
msgstr "And yet the Buddha tells me to act after careful consideration. "

msgctxt "an8.12:26.6"
msgid "Esāhaṃ, bhante, dutiyampi bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca. "
msgstr "For a second time, I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "an8.12:26.7"
msgid "Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti. "
msgstr "From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.186, sc27
msgctxt "an8.12:27.1"
msgid "“Dīgharattaṃ kho te, sīha, nigaṇṭhānaṃ opānabhūtaṃ kulaṃ, yena nesaṃ upagatānaṃ piṇḍakaṃ dātabbaṃ maññeyyāsī”ti. "
msgstr "“For a long time now, Sīha, your family has been a well-spring of support for the Jain ascetics. You should consider giving to them when they come.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.12:27.2"
msgid "“Imināpāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato bhiyyoso mattāya attamano abhiraddho, yaṃ maṃ bhagavā evamāha: "
msgstr "“Now I’m even more delighted and satisfied with the Buddha, since he tells me to "

msgctxt "an8.12:27.3"
msgid "‘dīgharattaṃ kho te, sīha, nigaṇṭhānaṃ opānabhūtaṃ kulaṃ, yena nesaṃ upagatānaṃ piṇḍakaṃ dātabbaṃ maññeyyāsī’ti. "
msgstr "consider giving to the Jain ascetics when they come. "

msgctxt "an8.12:27.4"
msgid "Sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante: "
msgstr "Sir, I have heard this: "

msgctxt "an8.12:27.5"
msgid "‘samaṇo gotamo evamāha—"
msgstr "‘The ascetic Gotama says, "

msgctxt "an8.12:27.6"
msgid "mayhameva dānaṃ dātabbaṃ, mayhameva sāvakānaṃ dātabbaṃ; "
msgstr "“Gifts should only be given to me, and to my disciples. "

msgctxt "an8.12:27.7"
msgid "mayhameva dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ, na aññesaṃ dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ; "
msgstr "Only what is given to me is very fruitful, not what is given to others. "

msgctxt "an8.12:27.8"
msgid "mayhameva sāvakānaṃ dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ, na aññesaṃ sāvakānaṃ dinnaṃ mahapphalan’ti, "
msgstr "Only what is given to my disciples is very fruitful, not what is given to the disciples of others.”’ "

#. VAR: samādapeti → samādāpeti (?)
msgctxt "an8.12:27.9"
msgid "atha ca pana maṃ bhagavā nigaṇṭhesupi dāne samādapeti. "
msgstr "Yet the Buddha encourages me to give to the Jain ascetics. "

msgctxt "an8.12:27.10"
msgid "Api ca, bhante, mayamettha kālaṃ jānissāma. "
msgstr "Well, sir, we’ll know the proper time for that. "

msgctxt "an8.12:27.11"
msgid "Esāhaṃ, bhante, tatiyampi bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṃghañca. "
msgstr "For a third time, I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "an8.12:27.12"
msgid "Upāsakaṃ maṃ, bhante, bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti. "
msgstr "From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc28
#. VAR: anupubbiṃ kathaṃ → anupubbikathaṃ (sabbattha)
msgctxt "an8.12:28.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā sīhassa senāpatissa anupubbiṃ kathaṃ kathesi, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "Then the Buddha taught Sīha step by step, with "

msgctxt "an8.12:28.2"
msgid "dānakathaṃ sīlakathaṃ saggakathaṃ, kāmānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ saṃkilesaṃ nekkhamme ānisaṃsaṃ pakāsesi. "
msgstr "a talk on giving, ethical conduct, and heaven. He explained the drawbacks of sensual pleasures, so sordid and corrupt, and the benefit of renunciation. "

msgctxt "an8.12:28.3"
msgid "Yadā bhagavā aññāsi sīhaṃ senāpatiṃ kallacittaṃ muducittaṃ vinīvaraṇacittaṃ udaggacittaṃ pasannacittaṃ, atha yā buddhānaṃ sāmukkaṃsikā dhammadesanā taṃ pakāsesi—"
msgstr "And when the Buddha knew that Sīha’s mind was ready, pliable, rid of hindrances, joyful, and confident he explained the special teaching of the Buddhas: "

msgctxt "an8.12:28.4"
msgid "dukkhaṃ samudayaṃ nirodhaṃ maggaṃ. "
msgstr "suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the path. "

msgctxt "an8.12:28.5"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma suddhaṃ vatthaṃ apagatakāḷakaṃ sammadeva rajanaṃ paṭiggaṇheyya; "
msgstr "Just as a clean cloth rid of stains would properly absorb dye, "

msgctxt "an8.12:28.6"
msgid "evamevaṃ sīhassa senāpatissa tasmiṃyeva āsane virajaṃ vītamalaṃ dhammacakkhuṃ udapādi: "
msgstr "in that very seat the stainless, immaculate vision of the Dhamma arose in General Sīha: "

msgctxt "an8.12:28.7"
msgid "“yaṃ kiñci samudayadhammaṃ sabbaṃ taṃ nirodhadhamman”ti. "
msgstr "“Everything that has a beginning has an end.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.187, sc29
msgctxt "an8.12:29.1"
msgid "Atha kho sīho senāpati diṭṭhadhammo pattadhammo viditadhammo pariyogāḷhadhammo tiṇṇavicikiccho vigatakathaṅkatho vesārajjappatto aparappaccayo satthusāsane bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Sīha saw, attained, understood, and fathomed the Dhamma. He went beyond doubt, got rid of indecision, and became self-assured and independent of others regarding the Teacher’s instructions. He said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "an8.12:29.2"
msgid "“adhivāsetu me, bhante, bhagavā svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghenā”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, may the Buddha together with the mendicant Saṅgha please accept tomorrow’s meal from me.” "

msgctxt "an8.12:29.3"
msgid "Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena. "
msgstr "The Buddha consented in silence. "

msgctxt "an8.12:29.4"
msgid "Atha kho sīho senāpati bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi. "
msgstr "Then, knowing that the Buddha had consented, Sīha got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before leaving. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc30
msgctxt "an8.12:30.1"
msgid "Atha kho sīho senāpati aññataraṃ purisaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then Sīha addressed a certain man, "

msgctxt "an8.12:30.2"
msgid "“gaccha tvaṃ, ambho purisa, pavattamaṃsaṃ jānāhī”ti. "
msgstr "“Mister, please find out if there is any meat ready for sale.” "

msgctxt "an8.12:30.3"
msgid "Atha kho sīho senāpati tassā rattiyā accayena sake nivesane paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyādāpetvā bhagavato kālaṃ ārocāpesi: "
msgstr "And when the night had passed General Sīha had a variety of delicious foods prepared in his own home. Then he had the Buddha informed of the time, saying, "

msgctxt "an8.12:30.4"
msgid "“kālo, bhante, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, it’s time. The meal is ready.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc31
msgctxt "an8.12:31.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena sīhassa senāpatissa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghena. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went to Sīha’s home, where he sat on the seat spread out, together with the Saṅgha of mendicants. "

# NOTE: BB’s “arms thrashing about” is incorrect. It means this http://previews.123rf.com/images/atic12/atic121402/atic12140200595/25885329-Closeup-portrait-of-overwhelmed-depressed-unhappy-upset-young-beautiful-woman-with-arms-raised-in-ai-Stock-Photo.jpg Not this http://img.boatdeck.com.au/makethumbnail.php?src=/blogs.dir/78/files/2014/01/drowning.jpg&w=553&h=280&zc=1
#. VAR: rathikāya rathikaṃ → rathiyāya rathiyaṃ (si, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an8.12:31.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā nigaṇṭhā vesāliyaṃ rathikāya rathikaṃ siṅghāṭakena siṅghāṭakaṃ bāhā paggayha kandanti: "
msgstr "Now at that time many Jain ascetics in Vesālī went from street to street and square to square, calling out with raised arms: "

msgctxt "an8.12:31.3"
msgid "“ajja sīhena senāpatinā thūlaṃ pasuṃ vadhitvā samaṇassa gotamassa bhattaṃ kataṃ. "
msgstr "“Today General Sīha has slaughtered a fat calf for the ascetic Gotama’s meal. "

msgctxt "an8.12:31.4"
msgid "Taṃ samaṇo gotamo jānaṃ uddissakataṃ maṃsaṃ paribhuñjati paṭiccakamman”ti. "
msgstr "The ascetic Gotama knowingly eats meat prepared specially for him: this is a deed he caused.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.188, sc32
msgctxt "an8.12:32.1"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro puriso yena sīho senāpati tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā sīhassa senāpatissa upakaṇṇake ārocesi: "
msgstr "Then a certain person went up to Sīha and whispered in his ear, "

msgctxt "an8.12:32.2"
msgid "“yagghe, bhante, jāneyyāsi. "
msgstr "“Please sir, you should know this. "

msgctxt "an8.12:32.3"
msgid "Ete sambahulā nigaṇṭhā vesāliyaṃ rathikāya rathikaṃ siṅghāṭakena siṅghāṭakaṃ bāhā paggayha kandanti: "
msgstr "Many Jain ascetics in Vesālī are going from street to street and square to square, calling out with raised arms: "

msgctxt "an8.12:32.4"
msgid "‘ajja sīhena senāpatinā thūlaṃ pasuṃ vadhitvā samaṇassa gotamassa bhattaṃ kataṃ. "
msgstr "‘Today General Sīha has slaughtered a fat calf for the ascetic Gotama’s meal. "

msgctxt "an8.12:32.5"
msgid "Taṃ samaṇo gotamo jānaṃ uddissakataṃ maṃsaṃ paribhuñjati paṭiccakamman’ti. "
msgstr "The ascetic Gotama knowingly eats meat prepared specially for him: this is a deed he caused.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.12:32.6"
msgid "Alaṃ ayyo dīgharattañhi te āyasmanto avaṇṇakāmā buddhassa avaṇṇakāmā dhammassa avaṇṇakāmā saṅghassa. "
msgstr "“Enough, sir. For a long time those venerables have wanted to discredit the Buddha, his teaching, and his Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "an8.12:32.7"
msgid "Na ca panete āyasmanto jiridanti taṃ bhagavantaṃ asatā tucchā musā abhūtena abbhācikkhituṃ; "
msgstr "They’ll never stop misrepresenting the Buddha with their false, hollow, lying, untruthful claims. "

# NOTE: BB’s note on this accepts without question the notion that the Jains were vegetarians, which would make the argument of the current sutta, as he says, bordering on disingenuous. However it is quite well-known that Jain texts, including the earliest, the Acaranga, specify meat as allowable in certain contexts. See Acaranga Sutra 2.1.10.5-6 (http://www.sacred-texts.com/jai/sbe22/sbe2256.htm); Dasaveyaliya 5.1.73 and 5.1.84-86. This was accepted by at least some Jaina commentaries. Modern hesitancy over stating this plainly is a result of political lobbying by Jains: https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Jacobi%27s_letter_on_Acaranga_controversy_of_meat-eating Of course, whether this sutta accurately represents the Jains is a separate question. But clearly the difference is not as great as it might seem.
msgctxt "an8.12:32.8"
msgid "na ca mayaṃ jīvitahetupi sañcicca pāṇaṃ jīvitā voropeyyāmā”ti. "
msgstr "We would never deliberately take the life of a living creature, not even for life’s sake.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc33
msgctxt "an8.12:33.1"
msgid "Atha kho sīho senāpati buddhappamukhaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappesi sampavāresi. "
msgstr "Then Sīha served and satisfied the mendicant Saṅgha headed by the Buddha with his own hands with a variety of delicious foods. "

msgctxt "an8.12:33.2"
msgid "Atha kho sīho senāpati bhagavantaṃ bhuttāviṃ onītapattapāṇiṃ ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
msgstr "When the Buddha had eaten and washed his hand and bowl, Sīha sat down to one side. "

msgctxt "an8.12:33.3"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho sīhaṃ senāpatiṃ bhagavā dhammiyā kathāya sandassetvā samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmīti. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired him with a Dhamma talk, after which he got up from his seat and left. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an8.12:33.4"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

